Governor Dave Umahi of Ebonyi State has tested positive for COVID-19 and is currently in isolation, working from home. However, he handed coordination of the state’s fight against the pandemic to his Deputy, Kelechi Igwe. According to Governor Umahi, in a statement on Saturday, he and some of his close aides tested positive for the virus after undergoing out the test. In the statement, Umahi further disclosed that they were not showing any symptoms, but have since isolated, in line with protocols laid down by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control, NCDC. Umahi appealed to the people of Ebonyi State to follow NCDC protocols, just as he would be conducting all meetings virtually. Recall that by Friday(July 3), Ebonyi had recorded about 438 cases of the virus, according to NCDC. 357 persons have been successfully treated and discharged, with three casualties. Vanguard GOVERNOR David Umahi of Ebonyi State, Thursday, expressed worry over the manner some members of his cabinet were being infected by the dreaded Coronavirus as Ebonyi recently recorded 75 cases out of the over 3,000 samples tested so far in the state. June 5, 2020 In "News" By Peter Okutu - Abakaliki Governor David Umahi of Ebonyi State, Thursday, expressed worry over the way and manner some members of his cabinet were being infected by the dreaded coronavirus disease (COVID-19) as Ebonyi records 75 cases out of the over 3,000 samples tested so far in the state.… June 4, 2020 In "Coronavirus Updates" Two aides of Gov. David Umahi of Ebonyi have explained how they survived the deadly COVID-19 pandemic, saying that they were miraculously healed by God. June 8, 2020 In "News"